## 🚨 Containment Steps – SSH Brute Force Response

> **⚡ Execute all phases in order. Tick every checkbox. If ANY step fails, escalate to {{ on_call_engineer | default("the on-call SOC lead") }} immediately.**

---

### 🔴 Phase 1 · Immediate IP Blocking `(T+0 → T+5 min)`

> Goal: Cut off the attacker **before** any credential succeeds.

- [ ] **Block attacker IP on perimeter firewall**
  Apply DROP rule for all traffic from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` on **all** egress/ingress interfaces.
  Duration: `{{ block_duration | default("3600") }}s`. Rollback tag: `unblock_{{ source_ip | default("ip") }}`.

  ```bash
  # iptables (Linux host)
  iptables -I INPUT -s {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} -j DROP
  iptables -I OUTPUT -d {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} -j DROP

  # Schedule auto-unblock (rollback safety net)
  at now + {{ (block_duration | default("3600") | int // 60) }} minutes <<< \
    "iptables -D INPUT -s {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} -j DROP"
  ```

- [ ] **Block attacker IP on SDN controller** (PhantomNet network layer)
  Push flow rule via PhantomNet SDN API to drop packets from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` network-wide.

- [ ] **Enable SSH tarpit** – Delay attacker connections by `{{ tarpit_delay_ms | default(5000) }}ms` to waste attacker resources and gather more telemetry.

  ```bash
  # sshd_config – add tarpit (OpenSSH with EndlessSH or equivalent)
  # Alternative: tc-based delay
  tc qdisc add dev eth0 root handle 1: prio
  tc filter add dev eth0 parent 1: protocol ip u32 \
    match ip src {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}/32 \
    action delay latency {{ tarpit_delay_ms | default(5000) }}ms
  ```

- [ ] **Rate-limit SSH on host** – Apply `fail2ban` immediate ban for `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}`:

  ```bash
  fail2ban-client set sshd banip {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}
  fail2ban-client status sshd  # verify ban applied
  ```

{% if geo_block_country is defined and geo_block_country %}
- [ ] **Apply geo-block** – Block all traffic from `{{ geo_block_country }}` at the perimeter if attack campaign originates exclusively from that region.
{% endif %}

- [ ] **Verify SSH port `{{ ssh_port | default(22) }}` is still operational** – Confirm that blocking `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` did not inadvertently break legitimate admin access.

  ```bash
  # From an allowed IP on the SSH allow-list
  ssh -p {{ ssh_port | default(22) }} admin@{{ target_ip | default("<target_ip>") }} "echo SSH OK"
  ```

{% if ssh_allow_list is defined and ssh_allow_list %}
- [ ] **Verify SSH allow-list is intact** – Confirm the following IPs still have SSH access:
{% for ip in ssh_allow_list %}
  - `{{ ip }}`
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

- [ ] **Send `{{ alert_level | default("HIGH") }}` alert to SOC**
  Message: *"SSH brute force from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` on port `{{ ssh_port | default(22) }}` – `{{ failed_logins_threshold | default(20) }}` failures in `{{ timeframe | default("5 minutes") }}`. IP blocked for `{{ block_duration | default("3600") }}s`."*

{% if escalate_to_ciso | default(false) %}
- [ ] **🔴 Escalate to CISO** – This attack meets escalation criteria. Notify CISO at `{{ ciso_contact | default("ciso@phantomnet.local") }}` with incident summary.
{% endif %}

